                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/576.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-17T15:00:00-04:49">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">July</hi> 17, 1911—3 <hi rend="smallcaps">p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Furniss is advised by the Haitian authorities that a telegram has been
                    received announcing Gonaives in the hands of the revolutionists. The situation
                    makes the presence of a war vessel desirable at Port au Prince.</p>
            </div>
